Contributing to the VRP with Drones Project

First off, thank you for considering contributing to our project! Your contributions help improve the project and make it more valuable to the community.

How to Contribute
If you find a bug in the project, please report it by opening an issue on GitHub. Please include the following details:

* A clear and descriptive title.
* A detailed description of the bug.
* Steps to reproduce the bug.
* Any relevant screenshots or log files.

Suggesting Enhancements
We welcome suggestions for new features and enhancements. If you have an idea, please open an issue on GitHub and include:

* A clear and descriptive title.
* A detailed description of the enhancement.
* Any relevant examples or references.

Submitting Code Changes
1. Fork the Repository: Create your own fork of the repository by clicking the "Fork" button on the GitHub page.
2. Clone the Repository: Clone your fork to your local machine using:
    git clone https://github.com/gbencheikh/VRPD.git
3. Create a Branch: Create a new branch for your changes:
    git checkout -b feature-name
4. Make Changes: Make your changes to the code.
5. Commit Changes: Commit your changes with a descriptive commit message:
    git commit -m "Description of changes"
6. Push Changes: Push your changes to your fork:
    git push origin feature-name
7. Create a Pull Request: Go to the original repository and create a pull request. 
    Provide a clear and descriptive title and description for your pull request.

Code Style and Guidelines
Follow the existing code style and conventions.
Write clear and concise comments.
Update documentation as necessary.
Ensure that your code passes all tests.

Testing
Before submitting your code, make sure that all existing tests pass.
If you add new features, please include corresponding tests.

Code of Conduct
Please adhere to the Code of Conduct in all interactions with the project.